metadata.name: Fabric Remnants #38
metadata.description:
One of my sisters is a tailor and restorator. This piece is a homage to her. 
Shopping for fabric with her and seeing her atelier while she is working is a 
festival of color, shapes, patterns and a celebration of creativity.

This is my pragmatical take on her work. The fabric like texture and dashed lines
representing the yarn rearranged in a grid of leftovers.

The piece is a generated SVG, because of that it scales easily and is printable.

Use the arrow keys to toggle/tune some things & Space / click to regenerate a new
grid. The P key will toggle auto generation.

metadata.name: Everything flows #140
metadata.description:
The Generative Token is obtained in two stages: in the first stage warped noise is generated using the method explained by Inigo Quilez (see Licence.txt for reference); in the second stage, using Sobel method for edge detection, the noise gradient orientation is used to generate flow lines.

The first stage generate an image colored using the values of warped noise.
The second stage generate another image using gradient orientations both for shapes (the flow lines) and for coloring.
The two images are blended together to obtain the final result.

In both stages the color-maps are generated using a sinusoidal function of the gradient orientation angle with a random phases. There are 52 possible combinations of random phases.
Some palette used in the second stage are re-mixed using simplex noise with 20% of probability.

The user can save a 1200x1200 png with 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Four noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape (combined on a single number on the features)
- 52 generated color mapping for warped noise
- 52 generated color mapping for flow lines
- Blending of the two intermediate images

Features:
Grays: 25% of probability to have a grays palette, (True, False)
Color Palette: one of the 52 possible combinations of random phases
Color Mixing: 20% of probability to have a re-mixed palette
Noise Control: noise control parameter, (0 - 15)
Rare: when Grays = True and Noise Control < 4


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Zpritez 3D #374
metadata.description:
Generates interactive 3D pixel art sprites.
Each character also has a unique sound effect.
There are a variety of styles and backgrounds.
Click or touch to interact, position tweaks the sound.
Right click to save as a 1920x1080 image.

Code is based on my open source sprite generator ZzSprite.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzSprite

Audio is using my open source sound effect system ZzFX.
https://github.com/KilledByAPixel/ZzFX

metadata.name: Der Ast #194
metadata.description:
Der Ast is a work which grew from a love of triganometry. The tree grows and branches 
based on a fixed and finite set of rules and while this leads to some very self-similar 
structures, in some cases, it generally allows for some very detailed complexity and 
surprise overall.

In this system, a box is drawn and on top of it, a right-angled triangle. The triangle
has an α angle conforming to a set formula (for example, in one system the angle follows)
a sinewave along the bough). From this triangle we construct the next square/triangle
set upon the hypotenuse and, if the β is wide enough, a second branch sprouts from the 
adjacent side.

This work is intended to be printed, and so included are controls to allow you to download
a high-resolution version as well as to create any aspect you wish.

- Append &dpr=x to the URL where DPR is the pixel density you want. This defaults to 2
- Append &fs=true to the URL to scale the token to the size of your browser
- Append &width=x and &height=y to the URL to scale the token to a specific size

Double-click/tap to download.

metadata.name: Nullteilung #1
metadata.description:
Nullteilung is another exercise in suprematism and composition. Born from a series of exercises in subdevision and tesselation, it seeks to connect with the user through the creation of a sense of order and balance in the composition.

The term "Nullteilung" a German word that can be translated to "zero division" which is suggesative of the order and disorder paramount in the piece, working toward a goal of emotional and programmatic purity.

metadata.name: 7VV1N5 #81
metadata.description:
GO BIG OR GO HOME.

After a week of minimalism code, our hero, the handsome artist Daniel, decided he needed something involving maximalism to reset the balance. Finding pairs to put together is satisfying.

Images will take 6-9 seconds to display and refresh between window resizing.

Use the z key or single click/tap to switch to "zoom" mode, which zooms in and fills the viewport; use z & tap/click to cycle through views. Use x and double-click/tap to go back to square mode.

Note: It doesn't work on Internet Explorer, because Microsoft. iOS is faster than Android.

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

z, click, tap - Switch to & cycle "zoom" mode
x, double-click, double-tap - Switch back out of "zoom" mode.
h - Toggle high-res (slow)
s - Download and save image (takes a few seconds, longer for high-res)

metadata.name: BlockonBlock #73
metadata.description:
‘BlockonBlock’ is the precursor and reserve pass for the upcoming ‘Hashway ‘69 Revisited’ collection by pixelwank. 
Free mint for pixelwank holders on tezos - After 3 days any remainders will be opened up to the public for 2tez.  

‘BlockonBlock’ was a study of rectangles following on from the use of circles in Generacci. 
Placements & building sizes are based on numbers from the fibonacci sequence. 

I had a blast making these and I hope they bring the collector as much enjoyment.

'Hashway '69 Revisited' coming soon :)

23 colour palettes 
14 colour overlays 
21% chance of extra lines
Click the image or press ‘s’ or ‘S’ in live move to save a 3000x3000 png 

Thanks for collectin’ & shoutouts to Circolors for the support <3 

R.I.F.F. 
Remember it’s for fun

metadata.name: Sap song #115
metadata.description:
This audiovisual generative artwork proposes sonorous green forms that flow excessively. Frenetic arpeggios and populations of plants are emerging, organized in their own way. And the sap sings, feeds and shows us a constructive desire for afforestation.

The work has 3 moments:
I. “Enredo coral”
II. “Recitativo libre”
III. “Coda hacia la raíz”

Original cello, marimba and music box samplers.

[s] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)

attributes.name: Information
attributes.value: Diurnal organic yellow version, in C# minor mode, for choir of 50 voices/plants.

metadata.description:

NOTE TO COLLECTORS:

This token will be sold as a Dutch auction. Every 5 minutes, the price will change based on the following schedule:
20 / 15 / 10 / 5 / 2 tez

After that, the price will remain fixed at 2 tez.
If there are tokens remaining after 72 hours, they will be burnt.

0xFoif

Inspired by Tyler Hobbs' water color studies and the splitting algorithm of 0xDrue, 0xFoif is a collection of interplay between a strong grid with clear cut splits and a blurriness introduced by multiple transparent layers.

Zürich/Quito, January 2022
❤️ pifragile

metadata.name: Balanced #105
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced
